onfirmed\n63\t- Error handling: ✅ API errors don't leak keys\n64\t- Rate limiting: ✅ Built-in protection\n65\t\n66\t**Code Review:**\n67\t```javascript\n68\t// Line 93 — Secure constructor\n69\tthis.apiKey = opts.apiKey || process.env.KALSHI_API_KEY;\n70\t\n71\t// Line 98-102 — Validates key presence\n72\tif (!this.apiKey) {\n73\t  throw new Error(\"Kalshi API key required...\");\n74\t}\n75\t\n76\t// Line 129-134 — Authorization header (secure)\n77\tconst headers = {\n78\t  Authorization: `Bearer ${this.apiKey}`,\n79\t  Accept: \"application/json\",\n80\t  \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\",\n81\t  ...(opts.headers || {}),\n82\t};\n83\t```\n84\t\n85\t**Positive Controls:**\n86\t- Requires API key at instantiation\n87\t- Demo mode by default (safe)\n88\t- Rate limiting prevents abuse\n89\t- Timeout protection on requests\n90\t\n91\t**Note:** Test key \"test_key_123\" on line 538 is safe — it's only for unit testing.\n92\t\n93\t---\n94\t\n95\t### 3. dashboard_api.js\n96\t\n97\t#### Status: ⚠️ CONDITIONAL PASS\n98\t\n99\t#### DASH-001 MEDIUM: Unauthenticated Pipeline Trigger\n100\t\n101\t**Location:** Lines 139-155  \n102\t**Severity:** MEDIUM  \n103\t**Issue:** POST `/api/run` has no authentication. Anyone with network access can trigger the trading pipeline.\n104\t\n105\t**Impact:**\n106\t- Unauthorized pipeline execution\n107\t- Potential excessive API calls to Kalshi\n108\t- Unintended trading costs\n109\t\n110\t**Current Code:**\n111\t```javascript\n112\tapp.post(\"/api/run\", async (req, res) => {\n113\t  const { spawn } = require(\"child_process\");\n114\t  // ... no auth check\n115\t  const runner = spawn(\"node\", [LIVE_RUNNER_PATH], {...});\n116\t});\n117\t```\n118\t\n119\t**Recommended Fix:**\n120\t```javascript\n121\tconst API_KEY = process.env.DASHBOARD_API_KEY;\n122\t\n123\tfunction requireAuth(req, res, next) {\n124\t  const auth = req.headers.authorization;\n125\t  if (!auth || auth !== `Bearer ${API_KEY}`) {\n126\t    return res.status(401).json({ error: \"Unauthorized\" });\n127\t  }\n128\t  next();\n129\t}\n130\t\n131\tapp.post(\"/api/run\", requireAuth, async (req, res) => { ... });\n132\t```\n133\t\n134\t---\n135\t\n136\t#### DASH-002 LOW: CORS Open to All Origins\n137\t\n138\t**Location:** Line 22  \n139\t**Severity:** LOW  \n140\t**Issue:** `app.use(cors())` allows any origin to access the API.\n141\t\n142\t**Recommended Fix:**\n143\t```javascript\n144\tapp.use(cors({ \n145\t  origin: process.env.DASHBOARD_ORIGIN || \"http://localhost:3200\" \n146\t}));\n147\t```\n148\t\n149\t---\n150\t\n151\t#### DASH-003 LOW: No Rate Limiting\n152\t\n153\t**Location:** Global  \n154\t**Severity:** LOW  \n155\t**Issue:** No rate limiting on API endpoints.\n156\t\n157\t**Recommended Fix:**\n158\t```javascript\n159\tconst rateLimit = require('express-rate-limit');\n160\tconst limiter = rateLimit({\n161\t  windowMs: 15 * 60 * 1000, // 15 minutes\n162\t  max: 100 // limit each IP to 100 requests per windowMs\n163\t});\n164\tapp.use(limiter);\n165\t```\n166\t\n167\t---\n168\t\n169\t## Summary Table\n170\t\n171\t| ID | File | Issue | Severity | Status |\n172\t|----|------|-------|----------|--------|\n173\t| - | live_runner.js | API key exposure | - | ✅ No issue |\n174\t| - | kalshi_client.js | Hardcoded secrets | - | ✅ No issue |\n175\t| DASH-001 | dashboard_api.js | Unauthenticated POST /api/run | MEDIUM | ⚠️ Fix before prod |\n176\t| DASH-002 | dashboard_api.js | CORS open to all | LOW | ⚠️ Fix before prod |\n177\t| DASH-003 | dashboard_api.js | No rate limiting | LOW | ℹ️ Recommended |\n178\t\n179\t---\n180\t\n181\t## Recommendations\n182\t\n183\t1. **Before Production:**\n184\t   - Add authentication to POST /api/run (DASH-001)\n185\t   - Restrict CORS to dashboard origin (DASH-002)\n186\t   - Add rate limiting (DASH-003)\n187\t\n188\t2. **Environment Variables Needed:**\n189\t   - `DASHBOARD_API_KEY` — for API authentication\n190\t   - `DASHBOARD_ORIGIN` — for CORS restriction\n191\t\n192\t3. **Deployment Checklist:**\n193\t   - [ ] KALSHI_API_KEY set in production\n194\t   - [ ] DASHBOARD_API_KEY set in production\n195\t   - [ ] DASHBOARD_ORIGIN configured\n196\t   - [ ] Rate limiting enabled\n197\t\n198\t---\n199\t\n200\t## Conclusion\n201\t\n202\tThe trading pipeline is **secure for development/demo use**. The only blocking issue for production is DASH-001 (unauthenticated pipeline trigger). All API key handling is correct — no keys are exposed in code, logs, or error messages.\n203\t\n204\t**Task 261: COMPLETE**\n205\t\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d03b287f-0136-4f74-aaf9-d4261714ac7a","uuid":"108ccab8-ad68-43ca-be89-17aaada0b950","timestamp":"2026-04-03T17:05:01.248Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/agents/heidi/output/security_audit_261.md","content":"# Security Audit Report — Task 261\n**Auditor:** Heidi (Security Engineer)  \n**Date:** 2026-04-03  \n**Scope:** Trading Pipeline Security Review\n\n## Files Audited\n1. `agents/bob/backend/strategies/live_runner.js`\n2. `agents/bob/backend/kalshi_client.js`\n3. `agents/bob/backend/dashboard_api.js`\n\n---\n\n## Executive Summary\n\n| File | Status | Findings |\n|------|--------|----------|\n| live_runner.js | ✅ PASS | No issues found |\n| kalshi_client.js | ✅ PASS | No issues found |\n| dashboard_api.js | ⚠️ CONDITIONAL PASS | 1 MEDIUM, 2 LOW issues |\n\n**Overall Risk:** LOW — No critical security vulnerabilities. Dashboard API needs authentication before production.\n\n---\n\n## Detailed Findings\n\n### 1. live_runner.js\n\n#### Status: ✅ PASS\n\n**Security Assessment:**\n- API key handling: ✅ Uses `process.env.KALSHI_API_KEY` (line 26, 223)\n- No hardcoded secrets: ✅ Confirmed\n- Error message leakage: ✅ Safe — error messages don't expose keys\n- Logging: ✅ No API keys in console output\n\n**Code Review:**\n```javascript\n// Line 26 — Correct env var usage\nconst USE_MOCK_FALLBACK = !process.env.KALSHI_API_KEY;\n\n// Line 222-225 — Secure client instantiation\nclient = new KalshiClient({\n  apiKey: process.env.KALSHI_API_KEY,\n  demo: process.env.KALSHI_DEMO !== \"false\",\n});\n```\n\n**Positive Controls:**\n- Graceful fallback when API key unavailable\n- Risk manager integration for trade validation\n- No sensitive data in output JSON\n\n---\n\n### 2. kalshi_client.js\n\n#### Status: ✅ PASS\n\n**Security Assessment:**\n- API key storage: ✅ Instance variable, not logged\n- No hardcoded secrets: ✅ Confirmed\n- Error handling: ✅ API errors don't leak keys\n- Rate limiting: ✅ Built-in protection\n\n**Code Review:**\n```javascript\n// Line 93 — Secure constructor\nthis.apiKey = opts.apiKey || process.env.KALSHI_API_KEY;\n\n// Line 98-102 — Validates key presence\nif (!this.apiKey) {\n  throw new Error(\"Kalshi API key required...\");\n}\n\n// Line 129-134 — Authorization header (secure)\nconst headers = {\n  Authorization: `Bearer ${this.apiKey}`,\n  Accept: \"application/json\",\n  \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\",\n  ...(opts.headers || {}),\n};\n```\n\n**Positive Controls:**\n- Requires API key at instantiation\n- Demo mode by default (safe)\n- Rate limiting prevents abuse\n- Timeout protection on requests\n\n**Note:** Test key \"test_key_123\" on line 538 is safe — it's only for unit testing.\n\n---\n\n### 3. dashboard_api.js\n\n#### Status: ⚠️ CONDITIONAL PASS\n\n#### DASH-001 MEDIUM: Unauthenticated Pipeline Trigger\n\n**Location:** Lines 139-155  \n**Severity:** MEDIUM  \n**Issue:** POST `/api/run` has no authentication. Anyone with network access can trigger the trading pipeline.\n\n**Impact:**\n- Unauthorized pipeline execution\n- Potential excessive API calls to Kalshi\n- Unintended trading costs\n\n**Current Code:**\n```javascript\napp.post(\"/api/run\", async (req, res) => {\n  const { spawn } = require(\"child_process\");\n  // ... no auth check\n  const runner = spawn(\"node\", [LIVE_RUNNER_PATH], {...});\n});\n```\n\n**Recommended Fix:**\n```javascript\nconst API_KEY = process.env.DASHBOARD_API_KEY;\n\nfunction requireAuth(req, res, next) {\n  const auth = req.headers.authorization;\n  if (!auth || auth !== `Bearer ${API_KEY}`) {\n    return res.status(401).json({ error: \"Unauthorized\" });\n  }\n  next();\n}\n\napp.post(\"/api/run\", requireAuth, async (req, res) => { ... });\n```\n\n---\n\n#### DASH-002 LOW: CORS Open to All Origins\n\n**Location:** Line 22  \n**Severity:** LOW  \n**Issue:** `app.use(cors())` allows any origin to access the API.\n\n**Recommended Fix:**\n```javascript\napp.use(cors({ \n  origin: process.env.DASHBOARD_ORIGIN || \"http://localhost:3200\" \n}));\n```\n\n---\n\n#### DASH-003 LOW: No Rate Limiting\n\n**Location:** Global  \n**Severity:** LOW  \n**Issue:** No rate limiting on API endpoints.\n\n**Recommended Fix:**\n```javascript\nconst rateLimit = require('express-rate-limit');\nconst limiter = rateLimit({\n  windowMs: 15 * 60 * 1000, // 15 minutes\n  max: 100 // limit each IP to 100 requests per windowMs\n});\napp.use(limiter);\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary Table\n\n| ID | File | Issue | Severity | Status |\n|----|------|-------|----------|--------|\n| - | live_runner.js | API key exposure | - | ✅ No issue |\n| - | kalshi_client.js | Hardcoded secrets | - | ✅ No issue |\n| DASH-001 | dashboard_api.js | Unauthenticated POST /api/run | MEDIUM | ⚠️ Fix before prod |\n| DASH-002 | dashboard_api.js | CORS open to all | LOW | ⚠️ Fix before prod |\n| DASH-003 | dashboard_api.js | No rate limiting | LOW | ℹ️ Recommended |\n\n---\n\n## Recommendations\n\n1. **Before Production:**\n   - Add authentication to POST /api/run (DASH-001)\n   - Restrict CORS to dashboard origin (DASH-002)\n   - Add rate limiting (DASH-003)\n\n2. **Environment Variables Needed:**\n   - `DASHBOARD_API_KEY` — for API authentication\n   - `DASHBOARD_ORIGIN` — for CORS restriction\n\n3. **Deployment Checklist:**\n   - [ ] KALSHI_API_KEY set in production\n   - [ ] DASHBOARD_API_KEY set in production\n   - [ ] DASHBOARD_ORIGIN configured\n   - [ ] Rate limiting enabled\n\n---\n\n## Conclusion\n\nThe trading pipeline is **secure for development/demo use**. The only blocking issue for production is DASH-001 (unauthenticated pipeline trigger). All API key handling is correct — no keys are exposed in code, logs, or error messages.\n\n**Task 261: COMPLETE**\n","numLines":205,"startLine":1,"totalLines":205}}}
