{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WZnz6KAeX9ZE4kUegdxgrQ","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Kalshi Trading System\n2\t\n3\tA full-stack trading infrastructure for Kalshi prediction markets. Fetches live market data, generates trading signals using multiple strategies, manages risk, and executes paper trades.\n4\t\n5\t**Target:** New engineers productive in 15 minutes.\n6\t\n7\t---\n8\t\n9\t## 1. Architecture Overview\n10\t\n11\t```\n12\t┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n13\t│                           KALSHI TRADING SYSTEM                             │\n14\t└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n15\t\n16\t  ┌──────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐\n17\t  │ Data Fetcher │────▶│  Strategies  │────▶│Risk Manager  │\n18\t  │              │     │              │     │              │\n19\t  │ • Kalshi API │     │ • Mean Rev   │     │ • Position   │\n20\t  │ • CoinGecko  │     │ • Momentum   │     │   Sizing     │\n21\t  │ • Grace's    │     │ • Crypto Edge│     │ • Daily Loss │\n22\t  │   Pipeline   │     │ • NFP Nowcast│     │   Limits     │\n23\t  │              │     │ • Econ Edge  │     │ • Exposure   │\n24\t  └──────────────┘     └──────────────┘     └──────┬───────┘\n25\t                                                    │\n26\t                                                    ▼\n27\t  ┌──────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐\n28\t  │  Dashboard   │◀────│   API Server │◀────│   Executor   │\n29\t  │              │     │   (Port 3200)│     │              │\n30\t  │ • Live Sig   │     │              │     │ • Paper Trades│\n31\t  │ • Edge Scan  │     │ • /signals   │     │ • Order Mgmt │\n32\t  │ • P&L Track  │     │ • /markets   │     │ • Fill Sim   │\n33\t  │ • Health     │     │ • /status    │     │              │\n34\t  └──────────────┘     └──────────────┘     └──────────────┘\n35\t```\n36\t\n37\t### Key Components\n38\t\n39\t| Component | File | Purpose |\n40\t|-----------|------|---------|\n41\t| **Data Fetcher** | `kalshi_client.js` | Kalshi API client with rate limiting |\n42\t| **Live Runner** | `strategies/live_runner.js` | Orchestrates signal generation |\n43\t| **Signal Engine** | `strategies/signal_engine.js` | Validates and filters signals |\n44\t| **Position Sizer** | `strategies/position_sizer.js` | Kelly criterion sizing |\n45\t| **Risk Manager** | `strategies/risk_manager.js` | Daily loss limits, exposure caps |\n46\t| **Execution Engine** | `strategies/execution_engine.js` | Paper trade simulation |\n47\t| **Dashboard API** | `dashboard_api.js` | Express server (port 3200) |\n48\t| **Dashboard UI** | `dashboard/index.html` | Single-page frontend |\n49\t\n50\t---\n51\t\n52\t## 2. How to Run the Full Stack\n53\t\n54\t### Prerequisites\n55\t\n56\t```bash\n57\t# Node.js 18+ required\n58\tnode --version  # v18.0.0 or higher\n59\t\n60\t# Install dependencies\n61\tcd agents/bob/backend\n62\tnpm install\n63\t```\n64\t\n65\t### Start the Dashboard (One Command)\n66\t\n67\t```bash\n68\t# Terminal 1: Start the API server\n69\tnode dashboard_api.js\n70\t# → Server running on http://localhost:3200\n71\t\n72\t# Terminal 2: Open the dashboard\n73\topen dashboard/index.html\n74\t# Or: python3 -m http.server 8080 --directory dashboard\n75\t# Then open http://localhost:8080\n76\t```\n77\t\n78\t### Start the Trading Pipeline\n79\t\n80\t```bash\n81\t# Generate signals (without executing)\n82\tnode strategies/live_runner.js\n83\t\n84\t# Generate signals AND execute paper trades\n85\tnode strategies/live_runner.js --execute\n86\t\n87\t# Output written to: output/trade_signals.json\n88\t```\n89\t\n90\t### Available Ports\n91\t\n92\t| Service | Port | Endpoint |\n93\t|---------|------|----------|\n94\t| Dashboard API | 3200 | http://localhost:3200 |\n95\t| Dashboard UI | 8080 (via python) | http://localhost:8080 |\n96\t| Kalshi API (demo) | 443 | https://demo-api.kalshi.com |\n97\t| Kalshi API (live) | 443 | https://trading-api.kalshi.com |\n98\t\n99\t---\n100\t\n101\t## 3. Environment Variables\n102\t\n103\tCreate a `.env` file in `agents/bob/backend/`:\n104\t\n105\t```bash\n106\t# Required for live trading\n107\tKALSHI_API_KEY=your_api_key_here\n108\t\n109\t# Optional: Use demo environment (default: true)\n110\tKALSHI_DEMO=true\n111\t\n112\t# Optional: Custom dashboard port (default: 3200)\n113\tPORT=3200\n114\t\n115\t# Optional: Database (uses mock if not set)\n116\tDATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:pass@localhost/kalshi\n117\t```\n118\t\n119\t### Getting Your API Key\n120\t\n121\t1. Register at https://kalshi.com/signup\n122\t2. Complete KYC verification (required by CFTC)\n123\t3. Go to Settings → API Keys\n124\t4. Generate a new key (scope: \"Trading\" for live, \"Demo\" for paper)\n125\t5. Copy the key to your `.env` file\n126\t\n127\t### Without API Key\n128\t\n129\tThe system works without a key using **mock fallback data**:\n130\t- Realistic market data for 5+ markets\n131\t- Simulated signals from all strategies\n132\t- Full dashboard functionality\n133\t- Paper trades execute against simulated fills\n134\t\n135\t---\n136\t\n137\t## 4. How to Run Backtests\n138\t\n139\t### Quick Backtest\n140\t\n141\t```bash\n142\t# Run strategies against historical data\n143\tnode strategies/backtest.js --strategy=mean_reversion --days=30\n144\t\n145\t# Output: output/backtest_results.json\n146\t```\n147\t\n148\t### Full Backtest Suite\n149\t\n150\t```bash\n151\t# Test all strategies\n152\tnode strategies/backtest.js --all --days=90 --report\n153\t\n154\t# Generates:\n155\t# - output/backtest_summary.md\n156\t# - output/backtest_charts.html\n157\t```\n158\t\n159\t### Backtest Configuration\n160\t\n161\tEdit `strategies/backtest_config.js`:\n162\t\n163\t```javascript\n164\tmodule.exports = {\n165\t  initialCapital: 10000,    // Starting balance in cents\n166\t  maxPositions: 10,         // Max concurrent positions\n167\t  commissionPerContract: 1, // $0.01 per contract\n168\t  slippage: 0.5,           // 0.5% slippage on fills\n169\t};\n170\t```\n171\t\n172\t---\n173\t\n174\t## 5. How to Open the Dashboard\n175\t\n176\t### Option 1: Direct File Open (Simplest)\n177\t\n178\t```bash\n179\t# macOS\n180\topen dashboard/index.html\n181\t\n182\t# Linux\n183\txdg-open dashboard/index.html\n184\t\n185\t# Windows\n186\tstart dashboard/index.html\n187\t```\n188\t\n189\t### Option 2: Local Server (Recommended)\n190\t\n191\t```bash\n192\tcd dashboard\n193\tpython3 -m http.server 8080\n194\t\n195\t# Open http://localhost:8080\n196\t```\n197\t\n198\t### Option 3: With Live API\n199\t\n200\t```bash\n201\t# Terminal 1\n202\tnode dashboard_api.js\n203\t\n204\t# Terminal 2\n205\tpython3 -m http.server 8080 --directory dashboard\n206\t\n207\t# Open http://localhost:8080\n208\t# Dashboard fetches from http://localhost:3200/api/*\n209\t```\n210\t\n211\t### Dashboard Features\n212\t\n213\t| Panel | Description | Auto-Refresh |\n214\t|-------|-------------|--------------|\n215\t| **Live Signals** | Current trading signals with color coding | 60s |\n216\t| **Edge Scanner** | Top 10 markets by edge magnitude | 60s |\n217\t| **P&L Tracker** | Paper trading performance | 60s |\n218\t| **Strategy Health** | Status of all strategies | 60s |\n219\t| **Run Pipeline** | Manual trigger for signal generation | On click |\n220\t\n221\t---\n222\t\n223\t## 6. Deployment Notes\n224\t\n225\t### Docker Deployment\n226\t\n227\t```dockerfile\n228\t# Dockerfile\n229\tFROM node:18-alpine\n230\tWORKDIR /app\n231\tCOPY package*.json ./\n232\tRUN npm install\n233\tCOPY . .\n234\tEXPOSE 3200\n235\tCMD [\"node\", \"dashboard_api.js\"]\n236\t```\n237\t\n238\t```bash\n239\t# Build and run\n240\tdocker build -t kalshi-trading .\n241\tdocker run -p 3200:3200 --env-file .env kalshi-trading\n242\t```\n243\t\n244\t### Production Checklist\n245\t\n246\t- [ ] Set `KALSHI_API_KEY` (production key)\n247\t- [ ] Set `KALSHI_DEMO=false`\n248\t- [ ] Configure `DATABASE_URL` (PostgreSQL)\n249\t- [ ] Set up log rotation (`logs/` directory)\n250\t- [ ] Configure monitoring (see `dashboard/monitor.js`)\n251\t- [ ] Enable rate limiting (already built into `kalshi_client.js`)\n252\t\n253\t### Security\n254\t\n255\t- Never commit `.env` files\n256\t- Use AWS Secrets Manager or Vault in production\n257\t- Rotate API keys quarterly\n258\t- IP whitelist if Kalshi supports it\n259\t\n260\t### Monitoring\n261\t\n262\t```bash\n263\t# Check system health\n264\tcurl http://localhost:3200/health\n265\t\n266\t# Check API status\n267\tcurl http://localhost:3200/api/status\n268\t\n269\t# View logs\n270\ttail -f logs/dashboard.log\n271\t```\n272\t\n273\t---\n274\t\n275\t## Quick Reference\n276\t\n277\t```bash\n278\t# One-liner to start everything\n279\tcd agents/bob/backend && node dashboard_api.js & python3 -m http.server 8080 --directory dashboard &\n280\t\n281\t# Generate signals\n282\tnode strategies/live_runner.js\n283\t\n284\t# Run with live execution\n285\tnode strategies/live_runner.js --execute\n286\t\n287\t# View trade signals\n288\tcat output/trade_signals.json | jq '.signals'\n289\t\n290\t# Check API\n291\tcurl http://localhost:3200/api/signals | jq\n292\t```\n293\t\n294\t---\n295\t\n296\t## Troubleshooting\n297\t\n298\t| Issue | Solution |\n299\t|-------|----------|\n300\t| `401 Unauthorized` | Set `KALSHI_API_KEY` env var |\n301\t| `EADDRINUSE` | Kill process on port 3200: `lsof -ti:3200 | xargs kill` |\n302\t| Empty signals | Check `output/trade_signals.json` exists |\n303\t| Dashboard not loading | Ensure API is running on port 3200 |\n304\t| Rate limit (429) | Wait 10s; built-in rate limiter will retry |\n305\t\n306\t---\n307\t\n308\t## File Structure\n309\t\n310\t```\n311\tagents/bob/backend/\n312\t├── README.md                 # This file\n313\t├── dashboard_api.js          # Express API server\n314\t├── kalshi_client.js          # Kalshi API client\n315\t├── kalshi_data_fetcher.js    # Data ingestion\n316\t├── dashboard/\n317\t│   ├── index.html           # Dashboard frontend\n318\t│   ├── monitor.js           # Monitoring alerts\n319\t│   └── run_scheduler.sh     # Cron scheduler\n320\t├── strategies/\n321\t│   ├── live_runner.js       # Main orchestrator\n322\t│   ├── signal_engine.js     # Signal validation\n323\t│   ├── position_sizer.js    # Kelly sizing\n324\t│   ├── risk_manager.js      # Risk controls\n325\t│   ├── execution_engine.js  # Paper trading\n326\t│   └── strategies/          # Individual strategies\n327\t│       ├── mean_reversion.js\n328\t│       ├── momentum.js\n329\t│       ├── crypto_edge.js\n330\t│       ├── nfp_nowcast.js\n331\t│       └── econ_edge.js\n332\t├── db/\n333\t│   └── schema.sql           # Database schema\n334\t└── output/\n335\t    └── trade_signals.json   # Generated signals\n336\t```\n337\t\n338\t---\n339\t\n340\t**Questions?** Check `output/kalshi_credentials.md` for API setup help or ping Alice in `#trading-ops`.\n341\t\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d03b287f-0136-4f74-aaf9-d4261714ac7a","uuid":"21040c9c-cd03-4fac-9358-ef11f009cf05","timestamp":"2026-04-03T17:05:01.380Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/agents/bob/backend/README.md","content":"# Kalshi Trading System\n\nA full-stack trading infrastructure for Kalshi prediction markets. Fetches live market data, generates trading signals using multiple strategies, manages risk, and executes paper trades.\n\n**Target:** New engineers productive in 15 minutes.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Architecture Overview\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                           KALSHI TRADING SYSTEM                             │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n\n  ┌──────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐\n  │ Data Fetcher │────▶│  Strategies  │────▶│Risk Manager  │\n  │              │     │              │     │              │\n  │ • Kalshi API │     │ • Mean Rev   │     │ • Position   │\n  │ • CoinGecko  │     │ • Momentum   │     │   Sizing     │\n  │ • Grace's    │     │ • Crypto Edge│     │ • Daily Loss │\n  │   Pipeline   │     │ • NFP Nowcast│     │   Limits     │\n  │              │     │ • Econ Edge  │     │ • Exposure   │\n  └──────────────┘     └──────────────┘     └──────┬───────┘\n                                                    │\n                                                    ▼\n  ┌──────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐\n  │  Dashboard   │◀────│   API Server │◀────│   Executor   │\n  │              │     │   (Port 3200)│     │              │\n  │ • Live Sig   │     │              │     │ • Paper Trades│\n  │ • Edge Scan  │     │ • /signals   │     │ • Order Mgmt │\n  │ • P&L Track  │     │ • /markets   │     │ • Fill Sim   │\n  │ • Health     │     │ • /status    │     │              │\n  └──────────────┘     └──────────────┘     └──────────────┘\n```\n\n### Key Components\n\n| Component | File | Purpose |\n|-----------|------|---------|\n| **Data Fetcher** | `kalshi_client.js` | Kalshi API client with rate limiting |\n| **Live Runner** | `strategies/live_runner.js` | Orchestrates signal generation |\n| **Signal Engine** | `strategies/signal_engine.js` | Validates and filters signals |\n| **Position Sizer** | `strategies/position_sizer.js` | Kelly criterion sizing |\n| **Risk Manager** | `strategies/risk_manager.js` | Daily loss limits, exposure caps |\n| **Execution Engine** | `strategies/execution_engine.js` | Paper trade simulation |\n| **Dashboard API** | `dashboard_api.js` | Express server (port 3200) |\n| **Dashboard UI** | `dashboard/index.html` | Single-page frontend |\n\n---\n\n## 2. How to Run the Full Stack\n\n### Prerequisites\n\n```bash\n# Node.js 18+ required\nnode --version  # v18.0.0 or higher\n\n# Install dependencies\ncd agents/bob/backend\nnpm install\n```\n\n### Start the Dashboard (One Command)\n\n```bash\n# Terminal 1: Start the API server\nnode dashboard_api.js\n# → Server running on http://localhost:3200\n\n# Terminal 2: Open the dashboard\nopen dashboard/index.html\n# Or: python3 -m http.server 8080 --directory dashboard\n# Then open http://localhost:8080\n```\n\n### Start the Trading Pipeline\n\n```bash\n# Generate signals (without executing)\nnode strategies/live_runner.js\n\n# Generate signals AND execute paper trades\nnode strategies/live_runner.js --execute\n\n# Output written to: output/trade_signals.json\n```\n\n### Available Ports\n\n| Service | Port | Endpoint |\n|---------|------|----------|\n| Dashboard API | 3200 | http://localhost:3200 |\n| Dashboard UI | 8080 (via python) | http://localhost:8080 |\n| Kalshi API (demo) | 443 | https://demo-api.kalshi.com |\n| Kalshi API (live) | 443 | https://trading-api.kalshi.com |\n\n---\n\n## 3. Environment Variables\n\nCreate a `.env` file in `agents/bob/backend/`:\n\n```bash\n# Required for live trading\nKALSHI_API_KEY=your_api_key_here\n\n# Optional: Use demo environment (default: true)\nKALSHI_DEMO=true\n\n# Optional: Custom dashboard port (default: 3200)\nPORT=3200\n\n# Optional: Database (uses mock if not set)\nDATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:pass@localhost/kalshi\n```\n\n### Getting Your API Key\n\n1. Register at https://kalshi.com/signup\n2. Complete KYC verification (required by CFTC)\n3. Go to Settings → API Keys\n4. Generate a new key (scope: \"Trading\" for live, \"Demo\" for paper)\n5. Copy the key to your `.env` file\n\n### Without API Key\n\nThe system works without a key using **mock fallback data**:\n- Realistic market data for 5+ markets\n- Simulated signals from all strategies\n- Full dashboard functionality\n- Paper trades execute against simulated fills\n\n---\n\n## 4. How to Run Backtests\n\n### Quick Backtest\n\n```bash\n# Run strategies against historical data\nnode strategies/backtest.js --strategy=mean_reversion --days=30\n\n# Output: output/backtest_results.json\n```\n\n### Full Backtest Suite\n\n```bash\n# Test all strategies\nnode strategies/backtest.js --all --days=90 --report\n\n# Generates:\n# - output/backtest_summary.md\n# - output/backtest_charts.html\n```\n\n### Backtest Configuration\n\nEdit `strategies/backtest_config.js`:\n\n```javascript\nmodule.exports = {\n  initialCapital: 10000,    // Starting balance in cents\n  maxPositions: 10,         // Max concurrent positions\n  commissionPerContract: 1, // $0.01 per contract\n  slippage: 0.5,           // 0.5% slippage on fills\n};\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. How to Open the Dashboard\n\n### Option 1: Direct File Open (Simplest)\n\n```bash\n# macOS\nopen dashboard/index.html\n\n# Linux\nxdg-open dashboard/index.html\n\n# Windows\nstart dashboard/index.html\n```\n\n### Option 2: Local Server (Recommended)\n\n```bash\ncd dashboard\npython3 -m http.server 8080\n\n# Open http://localhost:8080\n```\n\n### Option 3: With Live API\n\n```bash\n# Terminal 1\nnode dashboard_api.js\n\n# Terminal 2\npython3 -m http.server 8080 --directory dashboard\n\n# Open http://localhost:8080\n# Dashboard fetches from http://localhost:3200/api/*\n```\n\n### Dashboard Features\n\n| Panel | Description | Auto-Refresh |\n|-------|-------------|--------------|\n| **Live Signals** | Current trading signals with color coding | 60s |\n| **Edge Scanner** | Top 10 markets by edge magnitude | 60s |\n| **P&L Tracker** | Paper trading performance | 60s |\n| **Strategy Health** | Status of all strategies | 60s |\n| **Run Pipeline** | Manual trigger for signal generation | On click |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Deployment Notes\n\n### Docker Deployment\n\n```dockerfile\n# Dockerfile\nFROM node:18-alpine\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY package*.json ./\nRUN npm install\nCOPY . .\nEXPOSE 3200\nCMD [\"node\", \"dashboard_api.js\"]\n```\n\n```bash\n# Build and run\ndocker build -t kalshi-trading .\ndocker run -p 3200:3200 --env-file .env kalshi-trading\n```\n\n### Production Checklist\n\n- [ ] Set `KALSHI_API_KEY` (production key)\n- [ ] Set `KALSHI_DEMO=false`\n- [ ] Configure `DATABASE_URL` (PostgreSQL)\n- [ ] Set up log rotation (`logs/` directory)\n- [ ] Configure monitoring (see `dashboard/monitor.js`)\n- [ ] Enable rate limiting (already built into `kalshi_client.js`)\n\n### Security\n\n- Never commit `.env` files\n- Use AWS Secrets Manager or Vault in production\n- Rotate API keys quarterly\n- IP whitelist if Kalshi supports it\n\n### Monitoring\n\n```bash\n# Check system health\ncurl http://localhost:3200/health\n\n# Check API status\ncurl http://localhost:3200/api/status\n\n# View logs\ntail -f logs/dashboard.log\n```\n\n---\n\n## Quick Reference\n\n```bash\n# One-liner to start everything\ncd agents/bob/backend && node dashboard_api.js & python3 -m http.server 8080 --directory dashboard &\n\n# Generate signals\nnode strategies/live_runner.js\n\n# Run with live execution\nnode strategies/live_runner.js --execute\n\n# View trade signals\ncat output/trade_signals.json | jq '.signals'\n\n# Check API\ncurl http://localhost:3200/api/signals | jq\n```\n\n---\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n| Issue | Solution |\n|-------|----------|\n| `401 Unauthorized` | Set `KALSHI_API_KEY` env var |\n| `EADDRINUSE` | Kill process on port 3200: `lsof -ti:3200 | xargs kill` |\n| Empty signals | Check `output/trade_signals.json` exists |\n| Dashboard not loading | Ensure API is running on port 3200 |\n| Rate limit (429) | Wait 10s; built-in rate limiter will retry |\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\nagents/bob/backend/\n├── README.md                 # This file\n├── dashboard_api.js          # Express API server\n├── kalshi_client.js          # Kalshi API client\n├── kalshi_data_fetcher.js    # Data ingestion\n├── dashboard/\n│   ├── index.html           # Dashboard frontend\n│   ├── monitor.js           # Monitoring alerts\n│   └── run_scheduler.sh     # Cron scheduler\n├── strategies/\n│   ├── live_runner.js       # Main orchestrator\n│   ├── signal_engine.js     # Signal validation\n│   ├── position_sizer.js    # Kelly sizing\n│   ├── risk_manager.js      # Risk controls\n│   ├── execution_engine.js  # Paper trading\n│   └── strategies/          # Individual strategies\n│       ├── mean_reversion.js\n│       ├── momentum.js\n│       ├── crypto_edge.js\n│       ├── nfp_nowcast.js\n│       └── econ_edge.js\n├── db/\n│   └── schema.sql           # Database schema\n└── output/\n    └── trade_signals.json   # Generated signals\n```\n\n---\n\n**Questions?** Check `output/kalshi_credentials.md` for API setup help or ping Alice in `#trading-ops`.\n","numLines":341,"startLine":1,"totalLines":341}}}
