able documentation complete\n- Troubleshooting section covers common failure modes\n- Docker deployment notes included\n- Production checklist present (though Heidi's security items should be added)\n- **Minor gap:** Production checklist does not include DASH-001/DASH-002/DASH-003 items from security audit. Not blocking.\n\n### 5. Live Runner (`bob/backend/strategies/live_runner.js`)\n**Rating: PASS**\n\n- Correctly uses `process.env.KALSHI_API_KEY` (no hardcoded keys)\n- Mock fallback activated when no API key present — safe default\n- All strategies loaded: mean_reversion, momentum, crypto_edge, nfp_nowcast, econ_edge\n- Risk manager integrated before execution\n- Output written to `output/trade_signals.json`\n- `--execute` flag required for paper trade execution (safe default: signal-only mode)\n\n### 6. Dashboard API (`bob/backend/dashboard_api.js`)\n**Rating: WARN** ⚠️\n\n- Express server functional on port 3200\n- CORS middleware applied but unrestricted (`app.use(cors())`)\n- POST `/api/run` spawns `live_runner.js` without authentication — confirmed DASH-001\n- All other endpoints (GET) are read-only and low-risk without auth\n- **DASH-001 is the only blocker.** GET endpoints acceptable for internal paper trading use.\n\n---\n\n## Blockers (Must Fix Before Live Trading)\n\n| Blocker | Owner | File | Fix |\n|---------|-------|------|-----|\n| DASH-001: Unauthenticated `/api/run` | Bob | `dashboard_api.js` lines 139-155 | Add `requireAuth` middleware using `DASHBOARD_API_KEY` env var |\n\n---\n\n## Pre-Production Requirements (Before Going Live)\n\n1. **DASH-001** — Auth on POST `/api/run` (Bob)\n2. **DASH-002** — Restrict CORS to dashboard origin (Bob)\n3. **DASH-003** — Add rate limiting (Bob, recommended)\n4. Live backtest using real Kalshi price history (Grace)\n5. `KALSHI_API_KEY` set in production environment\n6. `KALSHI_DEMO=false` confirmed before live order placement\n\n---\n\n## QA Coverage Assessment\n\n| Area | Coverage | Status |\n|------|---------