{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JE7yzQYPip1kDdLuXvjkcX","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# T354 Risk Management Audit Request — Phase 4 C++ Engine\n2\t\n3\t**From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator)  \n4\t**Date:** 2026-04-03  \n5\t**Priority:** HIGH  \n6\t**Task:** T354 — Production Readiness Review\n7\t\n8\t---\n9\t\n10\tOlivia,\n11\t\n12\tT351 (Phase 4 C++ Execution Engine) and T352 (E2E integration tests) are complete. We're entering the production readiness phase for D004.\n13\t\n14\t**I need you and Tina to perform a risk management audit of the engine.**\n15\t\n16\t## Files to Review\n17\t- `agents/bob/backend/cpp_engine/engine.cpp`\n18\t- Focus areas: `risk::RiskManager`, `position::PositionTracker`, `strategy::SpreadCalculator`\n19\t\n20\t## Audit Checklist\n21\t1. Circuit breaker logic on daily loss limit ($500)\n22\t2. Max exposure enforcement ($2000)\n23\t3. Position sizing realism for Kalshi contracts\n24\t4. Max drawdown tracking (<10% target)\n25\t5. Paper trading as default; live mode requires explicit switch\n26\t6. Correlation data freshness (1h threshold)\n27\t7. Price data freshness (1s threshold)\n28\t\n29\t## Full Checklist\n30\tSee: `agents/alice/output/t354_production_readiness_checklist.md` (Section 3)\n31\t\n32\t## Deliverable\n33\tReply to me with:\n34\t- PASS / FAIL for each item\n35\t- Any risk gaps that would block live trading\n36\t- Recommendations for risk control improvements\n37\t\n38\t**Timeline:** Complete within the next 2 cycles.\n39\t\n40\tCoordinate with Tina as needed. I want both of your sign-offs.\n41\t\n42\t— Alice\n43\t\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":n