{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PLPmtHZcKuk7imFEc1dd1K","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# T354: Production Readiness Review — Go/No-Go Checklist\n2\t\n3\t**Task:** T354 — Production Readiness Review (Pre-Launch)  \n4\t**Owner:** Alice (Lead Coordinator)  \n5\t**Date:** 2026-04-03  \n6\t**Status:** IN PROGRESS\n7\t\n8\t---\n9\t\n10\t## Overview\n11\t\n12\tThis document tracks the production readiness of the D004 Kalshi Arbitrage Engine. No live trading may commence until every item in this checklist is signed off by the responsible party.\n13\t\n14\t**System Under Review:**\n15\t- Phase 4 C++ Execution Engine (`agents/bob/backend/cpp_engine/engine.cpp`)\n16\t- Input pipeline: `markets_filtered.json` → `market_clusters.json` → `correlation_pairs.json`\n17\t- Output: Paper trade logs → live order submission (Kalshi API)\n18\t\n19\t---\n20\t\n21\t## 1. Code Quality & Architecture Review\n22\t\n23\t**Responsible:** Alice + Dave\n24\t\n25\t| # | Item | Status | Notes |\n26\t|---|------|--------|-------|\n27\t| 1.1 | Engine compiles cleanly with `-std=c++20 -pthread -O3` | ✅ | Verified by Dave (T351) |\n28\t| 1.2 | All unit tests pass (24/24) | ✅ | Verified by Dave |\n29\t| 1.3 | E2E integration tests pass (14/14) | ✅ | Verified by Alice (T352) |\n30\t| 1.4 | No memory leaks detected (valgrind or ASan) | ⬜ | Pending Dave |\n31\t| 1.5 | Thread safety reviewed (mutexes, atomics, lock ordering) | ⬜ | Pending Dave |\n32\t| 1.6 | Error handling covers all fatal/recoverable/degraded paths | ⬜ | Pending Dave |\n33\t| 1.7 | Code documentation complete (headers, inline comments) | ✅ | High quality in engine.cpp |\n34\t\n35\t**Sign-off:** _________________ (Alice + Dave)\n36\t\n37\t---\n38\t\n39\t## 2. Security Audit\n40\t\n41\t**Responsible:** Heidi\n42\t\n43\t| # | Item | Status | Notes |\n44\t|---|------|--------|-------|\n45\t| 2.1 | API key storage reviewed (env vars, no hardcoded secrets) | ⬜ | Check engine.cpp + config |\n46\t| 2.2 | Kalshi API communication uses HTTPS/WSS | ⬜ | Verify URLs and TLS |\n47\t| 2.3 | No sensitive data logged to plaintext | ⬜ | Review log statements |\n48\t| 2.4 | Order router has auth validation before submission | ⬜ | Check `router::OrderRouter` |\n49\t| 2.5 | Input JSON parsing is safe (no injection, bounded buffers) | ⬜ | Review `CorrelationPairsLoader` |\n50\t| 2.6 | Network timeout/retry logic prevents hanging connections | ⬜ | Check libcurl + WebSocket paths |\n51\t\n52\t**Sign-off:** _________________ (Heidi)\n53\t\n54\t---\n55\t\n56\t## 3. Risk Management Audit\n57\t\n58\t**Responsible:** Olivia + Tina\n59\t\n60\t| # | Item | Status | Notes |\n61\t|---|------|--------|-------|\n62\t| 3.1 | Circuit breaker triggers correctly on daily loss limit | ✅ | Verified in T352 tests |\n63\t| 3.2 | Max exposure limit enforced in `pre_trade_check` | ✅ | Verified in T352 tests |\n64\t| 3.3 | Position sizing limits are realistic for Kalshi contract sizes | ⬜ | Review `suggested_contracts` logic |\n65\t| 3.4 | Max drawdown target (<10%) is measurable and tracked | ⬜ | Check P&L reporting |\n66\t| 3.5 | Paper trading mode is default; live mode requires explicit flag | ⬜ | Verify `demo_mode` vs live path |\n67\t| 3.6 | Correlation data freshness check prevents stale signals | ⬜ | Review `CORRELATION_FRESHNESS_US` |\n68\t| 3.7 | Price data freshness check prevents stale execution | ⬜ | Review `PRICE_FRESHNESS_US` |\n69\t\n70\t**Sign-off:** _________________ (Olivia + Tina)\n71\t\n72\t---\n73\t\n74\t## 4. Operational Readiness\n75\t\n76\t**Responsible:** Liam\n77\t\n78\t| # | Item | Status | Notes |\n79\t|---|------|--------|-------|\n80\t| 4.1 | Deployment runbook exists (how to build, start, stop) | ⬜ | Need document |\n81\t| 4.2 | Health monitoring / heartbeat is operational | ✅ | Engine prints heartbeats |\n82\t| 4.3 | Log aggregation strategy defined | ⬜ | Where do logs go? |\n83\t| 4.4 | Alerting thresholds defined (latency, error rate, P&L) | ⬜ | Need SLOs |\n84\t| 4.5 | Rollback plan exists (how to stop trading in <30s) | ⬜ | Need kill switch procedure |\n85\t| 4.6 | Binary can be rebuilt deterministically from source | ✅ | Single `g++` command |\n86\t\n87\t**Sign-off:** _________________ (Liam)\n88\t\n89\t---\n90\t\n91\t## 5. Compliance & Legal\n92\t\n93\t**Responsible:** Alice (with Founder approval)\n94\t\n95\t| # | Item | Status | Notes |\n96\t|---|------|--------|-------|\n97\t| 5.1 | Kalshi API terms of service reviewed | ⬜ | Founder action required |\n98\t| 5.2 | CFTC/regulatory considerations for automated trading | ⬜ | Founder action required |\n99\t| 5.3 | Paper trade validation complete (200+ trades, ≥40% WR) | ⬜ | Grace T353 |\n100\t| 5.4 | Go/No-Go decision documented and approved by Founder | ⬜ | Final gate |\n101\t\n102\t**Sign-off:** _________________ (Chenyang Cui, Founder)\n103\t\n104\t---\n105\t\n106\t## 6. Performance Validation\n107\t\n108\t**Responsible:** Alice + Dave\n109\t\n110\t| # | Item | Status | Notes |\n111\t|---|------|--------|-------|\n112\t| 6.1 | Spread calculation latency < 100µs | ✅ | 0.55µs measured |\n113\t| 6.2 | Order book cache update < 50µs | ✅ | 0.09µs measured |\n114\t| 6.3 | End-to-end latency target < 1ms | ⬜ | Needs full-path benchmark |\n115\t| 6.4 | Throughput: can handle 100+ market updates/second | ⬜ | Load test pending |\n116\t| 6.5 | All 6 arbitrage pairs detect correctly in integration | ⬜ | T356 validation |\n117\t\n118\t**Sign-off:** _________________ (Alice + Dave)\n119\t\n120\t---\n121\t\n122\t## Summary\n123\t\n124\t| Category | Passed | Pending | Blockers |\n125\t|----------|--------|---------|----------|\n126\t| Code Quality | 4 | 3 | None |\n127\t| Security | 0 | 6 | None |\n128\t| Risk Management | 2 | 5 | None |\n129\t| Operational | 2 | 4 | None |\n130\t| Compliance | 0 | 4 | T353 (Grace) |\n131\t| Performance | 2 | 3 | None |\n132\t| **TOTAL** | **10** | **25** | **T353** |\n133\t\n134\t---\n135\t\n136\t## Go/No-Go Decision\n137\t\n138\t**Status:** NOT READY F