{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_014gFv7T4P7CqabvNBtocz2T","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good findings. Now I have enough information to write the risk management audit. Let me compile what I've found:\n\n**PASS:**\n- 3.1: Circuit breaker triggers on daily loss limit ($500) - ✓ checked, config::MAX_DAILY_LOSS_CENTS = 50000 cents, enforced in pre_trade_check\n- 3.2: Max exposure enforcement ($2000) - ✓ checked, config::MAX_TOTAL_EXPOSURE_CENTS = 200000 cents, enforced in pre_trade_check\n\n**NEED TO VERIFY:**\n- 3.3: Position sizing - MAX_POSITION_SIZE = 1000 contracts, but is this realistic for Kalshi? Need to check what typical Kalshi contract sizes are\n- 3.4: Max drawdown tracking - I see unrealized_pnl tracked but no explicit max drawdown metric. There's a comment about <10% target but I don't see the calculation\n- 3.5: Paper trading as default - ✓ demo_mode = true hardcoded, no env var override. Good!\n- 3.6: Correlation freshness - ✓ CORRELATION_FRESHNESS_US = 3600000000 (1 hour), enforced\n- 3.7: Price freshness - ✓ PRICE_FRESHNESS_US = 1000000 (1 second), enforced\n\nRISKS:\n- Position sizing: 1000 contracts seems very high for actual Kalshi binary options. A single Kalshi contract is $0.01-1.00, so 1000 contracts would be $10-1000 per trade minimum. With max exposure of $2000, this could be realistic but RISKY.\n- Max drawdown: NOT EXPLICITLY TRACKED. The code tracks realized_pnl and unrealized_pnl but doesn't calculate max drawdown as a percentage of capital. This is a MAJOR GAP.\n\n\n- Demo mode lacks a PAPER_TRADING environment variable for control, which creates an operational friction point even though the hardcoded default is secure.\n\nNow I'll draft the risk audit report.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":179,"cache_read_input_tokens":54640,"cache_creation":{"